The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG and cs.AI the most likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of visual input (sensory streams) and dimensionality reduction techniques, which are common in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) research. Finally, the paper analyzes the distribution of level generators, which could fall under game theory (cs.GT).
